fields.name: Dango

fields.name: Tsukemen

fields.name: Tendon

fields.name: Ansim
fields.description: In South Korea, ansim is typically roasted on a grill

fields.name: Miso ramen
fields.description: Miso ramen is a flavorful dish made by cooking the miso base, broth, and vegetables in a wok.

fields.name: Century Egg
fields.description: A Chinese delicacy made by preserving duck, quail, or chicken eggs in a saline solution

fields.name: Agemono
fields.description: Foods are fried without a coating of flour or batter; karaage

fields.name: Char Kway Teow
fields.description: Savoury, flavorful flat wide rice noodles coated in a salty sweet soy sauce. Paired deliciously with pork belly, beansprouts, Chinese chives, garlic and egg.

fields.name: Ja Jangmyeon
fields.description: Jajangmyeon Black Bean Noodles. Thick wheat noodles smothered in a heavy black bean sauce with either pork or chicken, cabbage and onions.

fields.name: Chicken Ramen Bowel
fields.description: Ramen noodles smothered in a sweet soy sauce paired with tender juicy marinated chicken with a soy sauce egg, green onions and beansprouts.

fields.name: Chicken Pad Thai
fields.description: A delicious, savoury, sweet and sour stir-fried noodle dish

fields.name: Mee Goreng
fields.description: Thick chewy egg noodles smothered in a glossy, sweet and savoury sauce with pork belly, shrimp, fish cakes, Chinese chives and beansprouts

fields.name: Pad Woon Sen
fields.description: Delicious, chewy glass noodles covered in a soy oyster sauce accompanied with chicken, leafy greens and a red chilli vinegar.

fields.name: Hokkein Mee
fields.description: Savoury thick chewy egg noodles smothered in a brown sweet and salty soy sauce accompanied with prawns, pork belly, cabbage, and gai-lan.

fields.name: Sichuan Dan Dan Noodles
fields.description: Noodles smothered in a mala spicy chili oil, accompanied with hoisin flavoured pork and tangy preserved mustard greens

fields.name: Janchi Guksu
fields.description: Janchi Guksu (Warm Korean Noodles). A delicious comforting bowl of thin chewy noodles with soft boiled egg on top and a spicy kimchi sauce

fields.name: Bibim Guksu
fields.description: Korean Kimchi Bibim Guksu. Delicious chewy cold noodles mixed in a spicy, vinegary and sweet sauce!

fields.name: Wonton Mein
fields.description: Wonton Noodle Soup. Thin chewy egg noodles swimming in a chicken broth paired with pork wontons and leafy greens.

fields.name: Saba zushi
fields.description: Sushi rice base that is topped with marinated mackerel fillet, which is typically covered with a thin, delicate layer of kelp

fields.name: Tekkamaki
fields.description: Firm sushi rice, with a slightly acidic taste, is spread on top of nori, and the central part of the roll is a piece of raw tuna. Tender and soft, pink in color and mild in flavor, tuna perfectly balances the subtle flavors of nori and rice.

fields.name: Kiritanpo
fields.description: Kiritanpo is a traditional Japanese dish with origins in the Akita prefecture. It is made from cooked, half-smashed rice that is placed on a skewer, shaped into cylinders, then toasted over an open fire

fields.name: Injeolmi
fields.description: Injeolmi are traditional South Korean steamed rice cakes. They are prepared by steaming and pounding rice into a pliable dough which is then rolled and generously dusted with roasted soybean powder. The varieties include ssuk injeolmi, which incorporates mugwort powder, or kkaeinjeolmi, which is dusted with black sesame.

fields.name: Lotus Leaf Rice
fields.description: Lotus leaf rice (lo mai gai or nor mai gai) is a classic Chinese dish consisting of sticky rice wrapped and steamed in lotus leaves. The rice is usually soaked, seasoned with various condiments and spices, and blended with additional ingredients such as chicken, duck, mushrooms, shrimps, scallions, and salted eggs.

fields.name: Hosomaki
fields.description: One of the most popular makizushi varieties are the thin hosomaki rolls. They consist of traditional roasted nori sheets that are layered with vinegar rice, filled with just one ingredient, then shaped into thin rolls.

fields.name: Chirashizushi
fields.description: Chirashizushi is one of the most common sushi varieties prepared in Japanese households. This unusual version (often referred to as scattered sushi) consists of a bowl of sushi rice complemented with a wide group of ingredients that are either layered on top or mixed in the rice.

fields.name: Lo mai fan
fields.description: Lo mai fan is a traditional rice dish originating from China. It’s often served as a part of dim sum meals. Chinese sticky rice, as it’s also known, is made with a combination of glutinous rice, shiitake mushrooms, shrimps, soy sauce, Chinese sausage, scallions, salt, pepper, sugar, and sesame oil.

fields.name: Hokkien Fried Rice
fields.description: Hokkien fried rice is a popular Chinese rice dish originating from the province of Fujian. In order to prepare it, rice and eggs are first stir-fried together, then topped with a thick gravy made with poultry, dried mushrooms, seafood, and vegetables.

fields.name: Yangzhou Fried Rice
fields.description: Yangzhou fried rice is a Chinese dish consisting of rice, eggs, and vegetables such as carrots, mushrooms, peas, while the common additions also include shrimps, meat, scallions, and Chinese ham. Traditional versions often may incorporate sea cucumbers, crab meat, and bamboo shoots.

fields.name: Chamchi gimbap
fields.description: This gimbap (Korean rice roll) is made with canned tuna. Apart from rice and fish, the fillings may include other ingredients that are typically used in gimbap such as fresh or pickled vegetables, eggs, or fish cakes, while the tuna is often mashed and then combined with mayonnaise, mustard, and spices.

fields.name: Crispy Sweet Chilli Chicken
fields.description: Chinese crispy shredded chicken coated in a sweet and chilli sauce.

fields.name: Thai Sweet & Sour Chicken
fields.image_url: Thai sweet and sour chicken with added chilli sauce. A rich spicy and sweet flavour that will melt in your mouth.

fields.name: Crispy Roast Duck
fields.description: Roast Duck Served with Asian vegetables and Plum sauce.

fields.name: Sambal Sauce
fields.description: Wok fried mixed vegetables in our homemade sambal paste.

fields.name: Chilli & Cashew Nut
fields.description: With Mixed vegetable and cashew nuts, dry Chilli.

fields.name: Pad Kha Pao
fields.description: With fresh garlic, chilli, onion, carrot, mixed pepper, mushroom and sweet basil.

fields.name: Pad Prik
fields.description: Mixed pepper, onion, carrot and mushroom with black bean sauce.

fields.name: Pad King
fields.description: Ginger, mixed peppers ,onion, carrot and spring onion fried in seasoning sauce.

fields.name: Malay BBQ Honey
fields.description: Stir fried mixed pepper, onion, carrot in Malaysian style BBQ sauce

fields.name: Chilli & Thai Herbs
fields.description: Stir fried chilli, mixed pepper, carrot , Thai herbs with fine beans and basil leaves.

fields.name: Chilli Satay Sauce
fields.description: Stir fried onion, carrot, mixed peppers, peanuts in Malaysian satay sauce.

fields.name: Egg Roll Soup
fields.description: This Egg Roll Soup recipe brings together all of those irresistible egg roll flavors we love…in a soup!!

fields.name: Thai Coconut Curry Chicken Soup
fields.description: This coconut curry soup with chicken and chickpeas is so filling and satisfying, it’s hard to believe that it qualifies as health food—but we promise, it really, really does

fields.name: Vegan Yellow Curry Noodle Bowls
fields.description: This simple vegan yellow curry with noodles and coconut milk is made with pantry staples like ginger and turmeric, leaving out any harder to find ingredients for a quick and easy colourful noodle bowl. Packed with veggies and naturally gluten free.

fields.name: Orange Tofu
fields.description: This crispy vegan orange tofu is so simple to make, low-oil and made with just a few natural ingredients

fields.name: Vegetable Stir Fry with Creamy Peanut Sauce
fields.description: A delicious peanut sauce compliments this fantastic stir fry. Thai spices with Chinese herbs.

fields.name: Vegan Miso Soup
fields.description: This delicious homemade vegan miso soup recipe is so flavorful and comforting. Made with vegetable broth, veggies and tofu!

fields.name: Vegan Vegetable Lo Mein
fields.description: All the benefits of a Lo Mein but with Tofu. Chinese vegetables and Japanese herbs to compliment. You won't be disappointed!!

fields.name: Crispy Baked Peanut Tofu with Pickled Shallots and Fresh Herbs
fields.description: Baked to perfection!! Our chefs have created a complimented dish that was inspired by each culture we share here at FineChop. Tangy pickled shallots and fresh herbs from our gardens.

fields.name: Thai Crunch Salad with Peanut Dressing
fields.description: It's made with crisp Napa cabbage, crunchy vegetables and edamame but it's the creamy peanut dressing that makes it so good.

fields.name: Thai Quinoa Salad with Fresh Herbs & Lime Vinaigrette
fields.description: This flavorful Thai quinoa salad packed with protein and fresh veggies is a healthy eater's dream!

fields.name: Asian Slaw with Ginger Peanut Dressing
fields.description: This Asian slaw is a great way to eat your colors, and it's every bit as delicious as it is healthful.

fields.name: Thai Cucumber Salad with Peanuts
fields.description: This light cucumber salad is one of my warm weather staples. The dressing is tangy and sweet, and the peanuts add a welcome salty crunch. The best part is that the juice from the cucumbers seeps into the dressing, giving it a delicious cucumber flavor.

fields.name: Thai Spicy Duck Salad
fields.description: Roast duck served with mixed salad and Thai chilli & lime dressing

fields.name: Thai Prawn Crackers
fields.description: Manora Uncooked Thai Prawn Crackers are made from high quality, fresh shrimp, no artificial colouring added. Delicious and crispy, once cooked these shrimp chips are an ideal snack for adults and children alike. For better taste, try with chilli or tomato sauce.

fields.name: Steamed Jasmine Rice
fields.description: Jasmine rice is a particularly fine, medium-grain type of rice. It is fragrant when cooked, hence the name. The polished white rice is prepared without salt to balance the Thai flavors.

fields.name: Brown Rice
fields.description: Brown rice is a whole grain rice with the inedible outer hull removed.

fields.name: Egg Fried Rice
fields.description: Fluffy and aromatic egg fried rice is a crowd pleaser. A hearty meal on the go and a satisfying dinner after a hard day at work.

fields.name: Stir Fried Egg Noodles
fields.description: Whole grain noodles tossed with a heap of vegetables (whichever ones you have around) and your protein of choice (we used chicken) in a shortcut stir fry sauce.

fields.name: Rice Noodles
fields.description: Rice noodles, or simply rice noodle, are noodles made with rice flour and water as the principal ingredients

fields.name: Chips
fields.description: Chips are long, thin pieces of potato fried in oil or fat and eaten hot, usually with a meal

fields.name: Sweet Potato Fries
fields.description: Sweet potato chips are long, thin pieces of potato fried in oil or fat and eaten hot, usually with a meal

fields.name: Asian Greens

fields.name: Japanese Edamame
fields.description: Edamame is a preparation of immature soybeans in the pod, found in cuisines with origins in East Asia. The pods are boiled or steamed and may be served with salt or other condiments.

fields.name: Portion of Curry Sauce
